<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-14T09:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-14T09:45:00-05:00" n="463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.51/1902: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-14T09:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">March 14,
                                        1928—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 12:48
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>118. Cumberland sailed for New York on March 12. We have read the greater
                            part of the excellent report which he has prepared and are in accord
                            with his recommendations. Before his departure he discussed his
                            principal recommendation briefly and informally <pb facs="0639" n="529" xml:id="pg_529"/> with the President, the Minister of Finance and
                            General Moncada,<note n="68" xml:id="d463fn68">Head of the Liberal
                                Party.</note> all of whom expressed themselves as in complete accord
                            therewith.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>